```css
.panel {
  width: 200px;
  transition: width 300ms;
}
.panel:hover {
  width: 400px;
}
```

On hover, `width` changes on every frame of the transition.

```css
/* A: animate the box's position */
.card-a { position: relative; top: 0; transition: top 200ms; }
.card-a:hover { top: 100px; }

/* B: animate a transform */
.card-b { transform: translateY(0); transition: transform 200ms; }
.card-b:hover { transform: translateY(100px); }
```

Both move the card the same distance on screen.

The page has two animations running, then a click handler hogs the main thread:

```js
// Animation 1: a CSS transition of `transform` on a spinner (composited)
// Animation 2: a requestAnimationFrame loop that sets `el.style.left`

button.addEventListener('click', () => {
  const end = Date.now() + 500;
  while (Date.now() < end) {} // block the main thread for 500ms
});
```

This resizes 200 paragraphs to match a container's width:

```js
// `box` and `paragraphs` are fixed; box's width never changes inside this loop
for (let i = 0; i < paragraphs.length; i++) {
  paragraphs[i].style.width = box.offsetWidth + 'px';
}
```
